HEADWORD: Fashioner
<hw>Fash"ion*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who fashions,
forms, ar gives shape to anything.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>fashioner</qex> had accomplished his task, and the
dresses were brought home.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fashionist</ent>⟦br⟧
